<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="723" pageId="7" pageNumber="722" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,1089,1046,1582]" box="[113,1088,1046,1070]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<keyLead box="[113,1088,1046,1070]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">1 Pronotum less transverse, 1.30–1.60 times as wide as long. .......................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,1089,1046,1582]" box="[113,1088,1078,1102]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<keyLead box="[113,1088,1078,1102]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">– Pronotum more transverse, 1.60–2.20 times as wide as long. ....................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,1089,1046,1582]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
2 Antennae longer than body, antennomere III about 1.5 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[714,727,1110,1134]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">–</emphasis>
3.5 times longer than anntenomere II. Pronotum 1.3 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[324,337,1142,1166]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">–</emphasis>
1.4 times as wide as long. Aedeagus simple, long, thin, with one internal sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[243,323,1174,1198]" captionStart="Figs 66–69" captionStartId="26.[151,188,1519,1538]" captionTargetBox="[216,1055,416,1492]" captionTargetId="figure-45@26.[207,1071,413,1499]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 66–69.Aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view; ventral view). 66 – Hesperopenna vietnamica (Medvedev, 2000) (paratype); 67 – H. antennalis (Kimoto, 1989); 68 – H. minor (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype); 69 – H. bicolor (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740073/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity box="[479,611,1174,1198]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.95" metricValueMax="5.7" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="722" unit="mm" value="4.95" valueMax="5.7" valueMin="4.2">
4.2 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[513,526,1174,1198]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">–</emphasis>
5.7 mm
</quantity>
. .................... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[771,1088,1173,1198]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[771,1014,1173,1198]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hesperopenna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="722" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[771,1014,1173,1198]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">Hesperopenna pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,1089,1046,1582]" box="[113,1088,1206,1230]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<keyLead box="[113,1088,1206,1230]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">– Antennae shorter than body. ........................................................................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,1089,1046,1582]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
3 Larger species (body length 6.6–10.0 mm). Pronotum with very fine, almost indistinct punctures. Aedeagus long, robust, tubular, with basal orifice large and long (
<figureCitation box="[954,1076,1270,1294]" captionStart-0="Figs 11–14" captionStart-1="Figs 15–18" captionStartId-0="12.[151,188,1557,1576]" captionStartId-1="13.[115,152,1542,1561]" captionTargetBox-0="[158,1115,231,1431]" captionTargetBox-1="[126,1079,226,1362]" captionTargetId-0="figure-10@12.[151,1126,219,1436]" captionTargetId-1="figure-14@13.[113,1090,218,1370]" captionTargetPageId-0="12" captionTargetPageId-1="13" captionText-0="Figs 11–14.Aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view; c – ventral view). 11 – Hesperopenna medvedevi nom.nov.; 12 – H. persimilis (Kimoto, 1989); 13 – H. tibialis (Kimoto, 1989); 14 – H. arnoldi sp. nov. Scale bar 1 mm." captionText-1="Figs 15–18. Aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view; c – ventral view). 15 – H. bonifaci sp. nov.; 16 – H. helferi sp. nov.; 17 – H. sipekorum sp. nov.; 18 – H. zofka sp. nov. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740043" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740045" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5740043/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5740045/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">Figs 11–18</figureCitation>
). ..................................................................................... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[733,1088,1301,1326]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2013" box="[733,1014,1301,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hesperopenna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="722" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medvedevi">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[733,1014,1301,1326]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">Hesperopenna medvedevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,1089,1046,1582]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
– Smaller species (body length 3.7–7.0 mm). Pronotum with fine dense punctures, often with two or four small slightly elevated areas on disc. Aedeagus with relatively short proximal part, apex often bent down (
<figureCitation box="[451,531,1398,1422]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="27.[113,144,827,846]" captionTargetBox="[281,914,212,797]" captionTargetId="figure-172@27.[279,923,207,803]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Fig. 70. Aedeagus of Hesperopenna granulicollis (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype) (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view; ventral view). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740079" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740079/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
). ...................... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[708,1088,1397,1422]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Kimoto" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[708,1013,1397,1422]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hesperopenna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="722" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulicollis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[708,1013,1397,1422]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">Hesperopenna granulicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,1089,1046,1582]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
4 Aedeagus short, simple (
<figureCitation box="[423,505,1430,1454]" captionStart="Figs 66–69" captionStartId="26.[151,188,1519,1538]" captionTargetBox="[216,1055,416,1492]" captionTargetId="figure-45@26.[207,1071,413,1499]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 66–69.Aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view; ventral view). 66 – Hesperopenna vietnamica (Medvedev, 2000) (paratype); 67 – H. antennalis (Kimoto, 1989); 68 – H. minor (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype); 69 – H. bicolor (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740073/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
), without long dorsolateral projections. Antennomere III about 1.3–1.5 times longer than anntenomere II. Small species (body length 3.2 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1042,1055,1462,1486]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">–</emphasis>
5.0 mm). ................................................................................... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[780,1088,1494,1518]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Kimoto" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[780,1014,1494,1518]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hesperopenna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="722" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[780,1014,1494,1518]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">Hesperopenna minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,1089,1046,1582]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="722">– Aedeagus dorsolaterally with two thin processes, ventrally often with apical hook-like process or long projection from basal part directed anteriorly. ...................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="8" pageNumber="723">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1127,219,436]" pageId="8" pageNumber="723">
<keyLead pageId="8" pageNumber="723">
5 Aedeagus ventrally with or without apical hook-like process (
<figureCitation box="[861,942,219,243]" captionStart="Figs 66–69" captionStartId="26.[151,188,1519,1538]" captionTargetBox="[216,1055,416,1492]" captionTargetId="figure-45@26.[207,1071,413,1499]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 66–69.Aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view; ventral view). 66 – Hesperopenna vietnamica (Medvedev, 2000) (paratype); 67 – H. antennalis (Kimoto, 1989); 68 – H. minor (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype); 69 – H. bicolor (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740073/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="723">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
), always without long projection from basal part directed anteriorly. Antennomere III about 1.5 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1015,1028,252,276]" pageId="8" pageNumber="723">–</emphasis>
3.0 times longer than anntenomere II. Body length 
<quantity box="[630,761,283,308]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1" metricValueMax="7.1" metricValueMin="5.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="723" unit="mm" value="6.1" valueMax="7.1" valueMin="5.1">
5.1 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[663,676,284,308]" pageId="8" pageNumber="723">–</emphasis>
7.1 mm
</quantity>
. ..................................................... ..................................................................................... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[765,1126,315,340]" pageId="8" pageNumber="723">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[765,1052,315,339]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hesperopenna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="723" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vietnamica">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[765,1052,315,339]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="723">Hesperopenna vietnamica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1127,219,436]" pageId="8" pageNumber="723">
<keyLead pageId="8" pageNumber="723">
– Aedeagus ventrally with long projection from basal part directed anteriorly. Antennomere III about 1.3 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[322,335,380,404]" pageId="8" pageNumber="723">–</emphasis>
1.5 times longer than anntenomere II. Body length 
<quantity box="[880,1012,379,404]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.15" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="723" unit="mm" value="5.15" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="3.8">
3.8 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[913,926,380,404]" pageId="8" pageNumber="723">–</emphasis>
6.5 mm
</quantity>
. ............... ............................................................................................ 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[808,1126,410,436]" pageId="8" pageNumber="723">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Kimoto" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[808,1052,410,435]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hesperopenna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="723" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[808,1052,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="723">Hesperopenna bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
